{"_id":"YWJjNTFlOGJjZDE3","name":"Cultist","type":"npc","img":"worlds/lost-mine-of-phandelver/characters/015_-_Cultist/avatar.png","data":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""},"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"dex":{"value":12,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""},"min":3,"mod":1,"save":0},"con":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""},"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"int":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""},"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"wis":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""},"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"cha":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""},"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0}},"attributes":{"ac":{"flat":12,"calc":"natural","formula":"leather armor"},"hp":{"value":9,"min":0,"max":9,"temp":0,"tempmax":0,"formula":"2d8"},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0,"mod":1,"prof":0,"total":1},"movement":{"burrow":0,"climb":0,"fly":0,"swim":0,"walk":30,"units":"ft","hover":false},"senses":{"darkvision":0,"blindsight":0,"tremorsense":0,"truesight":0,"units":"ft","special":"passive Perception 10"},"spellcasting":"","prof":2,"spelldc":10,"spellLevel":0,"bar1":{"value":9,"min":0,"max":9},"bar2":{"value":12,"min":0,"max":0}},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<b>Picture: </b><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=JournalEntry data-id=OWJkZDhiMDg2NGRk ><i class=\"fas fa-book-open\"></i>Handout: Cultist</a><br/><br><p><strong>Cultists</strong> swear allegiance to dark powers such as  elemental princes, demon lords, or archdevils. Most  conceal their loyalties to avoid being ostracized,  imprisoned, or executed for their beliefs. Unlike evil acolytes, cultists often show signs of insanity in their  beliefs and practices.<br><br>\n\n<h2>Traits</h2><strong>Dark Devotion</strong>: The cultist has advantage on saving throws against being charmed or frightened.<br><br><h2>Actions</h2><strong>Scimitar</strong>: <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one creature. <em>Hit:</em> 4 (1d6 + 1) slashing damage.</p><hr><h4 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Roleplaying the Cultists</h4><p style=\"color: rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 )\">The cultists are not interested in fighting anyone and prefer to be left alone. The leader of the group is an evil and ambitious young man named Favric, who hopes to rise through the ranks quickly by earning the allegiance of the green dragon in area 7. His fellow cultists lack Favric's ambition and flee if he is captured or killed.</p><p style=\"color: rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 )\">If the characters talk to the cultists, Favric explains that they have come to treat with the green dragon (whose name he doesn't know). If the characters express a similar desire, Favric suggests an alliance. He really plans to offer the characters to the dragon as part of his tribute, and if a fight ensues, the cultists side with the dragon.</p>\n<hr><section class=\"secret\"><p><strong>GM Notes :</strong> </p><h3>Locations</h3><ul><li><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=JournalEntry data-id=ODQwMTJlYjA3ZWRi  style=\"background-color: rgb( 255 , 255 , 255 )\"><i class=\"fas fa-book-open\"></i>Ruins of Thundertree</a>: 13 (Favric)<br></li></ul></section>","public":""},"alignment":"Any Non-good Alignment","race":"","type":{"value":"humanoid","subtype":"Any Race","swarm":"","custom":""},"environment":"","cr":0.125,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":25},"source":"Roll 20","class":""},"traits":{"size":"med","di":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"custom":""},"ci":{"value":[],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":"Any One Language (usually Common)"}},"currency":{"pp":0,"gp":0,"ep":0,"sp":0,"cp":0},"skills":{"acr":{"value":0,"ability":"dex","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""},"bonus":0,"mod":1,"passive":11},"ani":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""},"bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"arc":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonuses